ABUJA  – The Revolutionary Social­ist Movement (RSM) has called on Nigerians to join the forthcoming mass ac­tion scheduled for January 27, 2022, against a plan by the Buhari led-government to increase the price of fuel. A statement signed by the Publicity Secretary, Sal­ako Kayode on Wednesday in Abuja asked Nigerians to resist and rise against the anti-people policies of the Buhari administration. The statement said that the Revolutionary Socialist Movement would actively support and take part in the protest just as it called on the organised Labour and Trade Union Congress (TUC) to come out with a plan of ac­tions to fight back against the anti-poor, neoliberal policies of the government. Barber Stabs Motorcyclist To Death In Bayelsa Novena University College Of Law Commences LL.B Degree… The group berated the Nigerian Government for always deceiving the masses by saying it is necessary to remove the fuel subsidy. The statement read, “The National Executive Council (NEC) of the Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) at its meeting of Friday 17th December 2021, decided to reject and resist the planned increase in the price of fuel by the Federal Govern­ment.